nodes.title: Flux Auto Inpainter with Lora Auto-Injection by EnragedAntelope
widgets_values:
Flux Auto Inpainter with Lora Auto-Injection
by EnragedAntelope
https://civitai.com/user/EnragedAntelope
https://github.com/EnragedAntelope

What it does?
This takes any input image and will replace the person/etc. of your choice with a lora, completely automatically. 
Masking and prompting is automatically taken care of!

It is dependent on an LLM. I recommend using a service as Flux already eats quite a lot of VRAM locally. Groq (as of this writing) offers free LLMs in the cloud, and Plush Nodes documentation (link at bottom) will help you get connected.

How to use: 
Everything you typically need to modify is directly under this note!

After initial setup of your LLM service and pointing Plush nodes to it... 
1. State what you want to change
2. Select a lora. 
3. Load a source pic. 
4. Queue prompt. Really, that's it. Every other setting should be good to go.

There is a special note in the masking section, in case the auto-masking is not working for you. The default solution has consistently worked for me in all of my testing, but I wanted to give you fallback options. 

Performance tip: If you have flash attention installed and working, switch both Florence nodes to use Flash Attention. I left it on a default option that should work for everyone.

Have fun!

Helpful links:
https://github.com/glibsonoran/Plush-for-ComfyUI?tab=readme-ov-file#requirements The awesome Plush nodes! Read up on how to connect to Groq or other services (you'll need an API key set in an environment variable)
https://github.com/idrirap/ComfyUI-Lora-Auto-Trigger-Words Super helpful Lora auto trigger words!

nodes.title: Auto-Masking Tips
widgets_values:
I suggest leaving this on my default. It will usually correctly capture your target area. 
However if this isn't working for you and/or you need a larger or smaller area, try another option. Masking all is essentially full image to image rework of the source pic, but it's there if you want to give it a go!
